Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Cases of Nipah virus infection occur sporadically in Bangladesh. The most recent major outbreak reported occurred last year (2011) at this same period of time. From 31 Jan - 5 Mar 2011, an outbreak in Rangpur region resulted in the deaths of 35 persons, including infants, boys, adolescents, and women (see ProMED-mail archive number 20110308.0756).

Scientists with villagers have constructed a type of "skirt" made of local materials that denies access of the bats to the palm sap collecting jars. Clearly, this simple technology needs to be spread around trough public education, particularly when the bats are pregnant and lactating, when the virus is shed.

An image of _Pteropus_ fruit bats, "flying foxes", can be accessed at the above URL.

